overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of a sleep questionnaire
  application, providing a detailed specification and an existing Statement of
  Work. The primary goal was to ensure all acceptance criteria were met and to
  implement any identified missing features. The agent conducted a thorough
  review, identifying several gaps, and then proceeded to implement these
  features. Key implementations included a 1-10 tiredness severity scale with
  safety warnings, detection logic for COMISA and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome,
  integration of external resource links, weighted scoring for Excessive Daytime
  Sleepiness, a complete CSV export of all questionnaire data, and new questions
  for pain severity and chronic fatigue screening. The implementation involved
  updating data types, validation schemas, UI components for input, and the
  logic for generating both on-screen and PDF reports. The agent systematically
  completed each task, ensuring the application now aligns more closely with the
  detailed requirements.
